TiO2 can serve as a medium in highly efficient PSCs. The Perovskite structure is defined as an ABX3 compound consisting of a corner-sharing BX6 octahedra, where X is an anion or halogen (generally iodine) with A and B cations of different sizes (A being larger than B). The larger A cation is usually an organic methylammonium CH3NH3+\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
